        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-29T07:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-29T07:35:00-05:00" n="441" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/11–2945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-29T16:00:00+03:25">November 29, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 30—8:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1023. Nabil says Governor General Bayat has gone to Tabriz with instructions to
                    follow policy of conciliation toward dissident elements most of whose leaders he
                    knows personally. He is to urge them to present their complaints direct to
                    Central Gov and assure them they will be given full consideration.</p>
                <p>Nabil asserts that although Bayat is <hi rend="italic">persona grata</hi> to
                    Russians he is not pro-Russian.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
